[SN]TITLE[SN]
Motorcyclist, 23, killed in crash in North Ayrshire

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A 23-year-old man has died following a road crash in North Ayrshire.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The man was travelling south on the A737, at Beith, when his Aprilia bike collided with a northbound Mercedes sprinter van and a BMW 3 series.
The accident happened near the B777 Gateside Road junction at about 18:35 on Wednesday.
Emergency services attended but the man died at the scene. The 47-year-old male van driver, and the 46 year-old male BMW driver were not injured.
Sgt Iain Pittams, from the Divisional Road Policing Unit at Irvine Police Office, said: "Inquiries are continuing into the circumstances surrounding the crash and I would ask any witnesses, or anyone with information that may assist our investigation to contact our office."
